# .trivyignore — acknowledged CVEs in pre-built binary tools
#
# These CVEs exist in pre-built binaries (gastown, dolt) that are already at
# their latest released versions. They cannot be patched without upstream
# rebuilds with newer Go toolchain/dependency versions.
# Re-evaluate when upstream releases new versions.

# CVE-2026-25679: net/url IPv6 host literal parsing (Go stdlib)
# In: gastown v0.12.1 (built with Go 1.25.7), dolt v1.84.0 (built with Go 1.25.7)
# Fix: upstream rebuild with Go >= 1.25.8
CVE-2026-25679

# CVE-2025-68121: crypto/tls unexpected session resumption (Go stdlib)
# In: gastown v0.12.1 or dolt v1.84.0 (built with Go 1.25.6)
# Fix: upstream rebuild with Go >= 1.25.7
CVE-2025-68121

# CVE-2026-33186: gRPC-Go authorization bypass via missing leading slash
# In: gastown v0.12.1 (grpc v1.78.0 and v1.79.2)
# Fix: upstream gastown rebuild with grpc >= 1.79.3
CVE-2026-33186

# CVE-2026-24051: OpenTelemetry Go SDK arbitrary code execution
# In: gastown v0.12.1 (otel/sdk v1.38.0)
# Fix: upstream gastown rebuild with otel/sdk >= 1.40.0
CVE-2026-24051

# CVE-2026-33671: picomatch Regular Expression DoS
# In: wrangler's bundled Node.js dependency graph in the globally installed CLI.
# This is a transitive vendored dependency inside the upstream tool bundle.
# Re-evaluate on the next wrangler upgrade.
CVE-2026-33671

# CVE-2026-34040 / CVE-2026-33747 / CVE-2026-33748
# In: Docker Compose plugin binary from Docker's official apt repository.
# The image installs the vendor-maintained plugin package rather than building
# Compose from source. Re-evaluate when Docker publishes a package with updated
# embedded docker/buildkit libraries.
CVE-2026-34040
CVE-2026-33747
CVE-2026-33748

# AsymmetricPrivateKey (secret/private-key) false positives
# In: /usr/local/install/cache/wrangler and miniflare JS bundles
# These are test-fixture private keys embedded in Cloudflare's tooling bundles —
# not real secrets. The install/cache directory is excluded via skip-dirs in all
# trivy-action steps. Listed here for documentation purposes.
